Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Creator Style Space", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"7b231a30-6029-4b76-a4ca-f092ce259074"],

Cell["Rijksmuseum Semantic Explorer \[LongDash] Notebook 3 of 5", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"8dc92f66-70db-4f42-bd8a-1d56d00c5099"],

Cell["\<\
Every artwork in the Rijksmuseum collection is associated with one or more \
creators. By aggregating the embeddings of all works by a given artist into a \
single centroid vector, we construct a derived \[OpenCurlyQuote]style space\
\[CloseCurlyQuote] where each point represents an artist rather than an \
individual artwork. This notebook explores that space: which artists are \
stylistically similar according to the embedding model? Do related artists \
cluster together in a hierarchical tree? Which artists have the most \
consistent output versus the widest stylistic range? The resulting creator \
map provides a novel, data-driven perspective on art-historical relationships \
within the Rijksmuseum collection.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7802bc71-080b-4739-899e-2ba670f2d969"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["1. Data Loading", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"f4b9d1a9-a950-47ca-983d-868b01581c97"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
dataDir = FileNameJoin[{NotebookDirectory[], \"data\"}];
If[!DirectoryQ[dataDir],
  Print[\"Data not found. Run: uv run python export_for_mathematica.py\"];
  Abort[]];
manifest = Import[FileNameJoin[{dataDir, \"metadata.json\"}], \"RawJSON\"];
{n, dim} = Lookup[manifest, {\"n\", \"dim\"}];
raw = BinaryReadList[FileNameJoin[{dataDir, \"embeddings.bin\"}], \
\"Real32\"];
embeddings = Partition[raw, dim];
artIds = manifest[\"art_ids\"];
artworks = manifest[\"artworks\"];
Print[\"Loaded \", n, \" embeddings\"]\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[214]:=",ExpressionUUID->"131e3307-032e-4579-8b0f-7a847974cc97"],

Cell[BoxData[
 InterpretationBox[
  RowBox[{"\<\"Loaded \"\>", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "20000", 
   "\[InvisibleSpace]", "\<\" embeddings\"\>"}],
  SequenceForm["Loaded ", 20000, " embeddings"],
  Editable->False]], "Print",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9815571138135433`*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "During evaluation of \
In[214]:=",ExpressionUUID->"1649ab04-a8ba-41a0-a79a-5c5f218f38ba"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["2. Creator Frequency Analysis", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"8f8fc7a3-fb91-48d2-b323-9d440ffcc4c0"],

Cell["\<\
The distribution of artworks per creator follows a power law, much like Zipf\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s law in natural language: a handful of prolific artists \
and large studios account for a disproportionate share of the collection, \
while the vast majority of creators appear only once or a few times. This \
long-tail distribution has practical implications for our analysis \
\[LongDash] centroid embeddings are most meaningful for well-represented \
artists, since averaging over many works smooths out individual variation and \
yields a robust style signature. We set a minimum threshold of 10 works to \
ensure statistical reliability. The log-log frequency plot confirms the \
Zipfian shape.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"daf70421-f110-4965-8567-4380b249abde"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
(* Primary creator for each artwork *)
creatorOf = Table[
  Module[{creators = artworks[ToString[id]][\"creators\"]},
    If[Length[creators] > 0, First[creators], \"unknown\"]],
  {id, artIds}];

creatorCounts = Counts[creatorOf];
Print[\"Unique creators: \", Length[creatorCounts]]

(* Top 25 most prolific *)
top25 = TakeLargest[creatorCounts, 25];
BarChart[Values[top25],
  ChartLabels -> Placed[Keys[top25], Below, Rotate[#, Pi/4, {-1, 0}] &],
  PlotLabel -> \"Top 25 Most Represented Creators\",
  ChartStyle -> \"DarkRainbow\",
  ImageSize -> Large,
  AspectRatio -> 1/2]\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[223]:=",ExpressionUUID->"4c50e2c6-ae96-4333-87e3-87bb4e16b6c6"],

Cell[BoxData[
 InterpretationBox[
  RowBox[{"\<\"Unique creators: \"\>", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "2761"}],
  SequenceForm["Unique creators: ", 2761],
  Editable->False]], "Print",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9815571183529587`*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "During evaluation of \
In[223]:=",ExpressionUUID->"c546eca3-4d73-438f-9bf7-ef563bc4cc23"],

