Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["3. Creator Centroid Computation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"dd1dd9a6-3ed2-4f3a-b744-3ef6e4429ca3"],

Cell["\<\
The centroid embedding of a creator is the L2-normalised mean of all their \
artwork embeddings \[LongDash] a single vector summarising the artist\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s average style as captured by the embedding model. For \
creators with many works, this centroid is a robust estimate of their \
stylistic centre of gravity; for those near the minimum threshold, it is \
noisier. We compute centroids for the top 100 most-represented creators, \
yielding a 100\[Times]384 matrix where each row is a \
creator\[CloseCurlyQuote]s style signature. This derived matrix forms the \
basis for all subsequent creator-level analyses: similarity matrices, \
dendrograms, and the 2D style map.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ad39dd9b-8a96-4a07-bedd-349d936b658a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
minWorks = 10;
qualified = Select[creatorCounts, # >= minWorks &];
topCreatorNames = Keys[TakeLargest[qualified, Min[100, Length[qualified]]]];
Print[\"Computing centroids for \", Length[topCreatorNames], \" creators (>= \
\", minWorks, \" works each)\"]

creatorCentroids = Association[Table[
  Module[{mask, creatorEmbs},
    mask = Flatten[Position[creatorOf, name]];
    creatorEmbs = embeddings[[mask]];
    name -> Normalize[Mean[creatorEmbs]]],
  {name, topCreatorNames}]];

centroidMatrix = N[Values[creatorCentroids]]; (* nCreators x 384 *)
nCreators = Length[topCreatorNames];
Print[\"Centroid matrix: \", Dimensions[centroidMatrix]]\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[235]:=",ExpressionUUID->"df6a2530-e1c8-49dc-aa06-bd05f40298f8"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 InterpretationBox[
  RowBox[{"\<\"Computing centroids for \"\>", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "100", 
   "\[InvisibleSpace]", "\<\" creators (>= \"\>", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "10", 
   "\[InvisibleSpace]", "\<\" works each)\"\>"}],
  SequenceForm[
  "Computing centroids for ", 100, " creators (>= ", 10, " works each)"],
  Editable->False]], "Print",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.981557131150085*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "During evaluation of \
In[235]:=",ExpressionUUID->"cc5f7485-0924-48bd-859e-90732987d4f2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 InterpretationBox[
  RowBox[{"\<\"Centroid matrix: \"\>", "\[InvisibleSpace]", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"100", ",", "384"}], "}"}]}],
  SequenceForm["Centroid matrix: ", {100, 384}],
  Editable->False]], "Print",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9815571312199*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "During evaluation of \
In[235]:=",ExpressionUUID->"65e55733-84c8-4d9b-bb25-9bc67ac25509"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["4. Creator Similarity Matrix", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6ff3be6a-9e44-4c38-954f-9f4480765e38"],

Cell["\<\
The creator similarity matrix shows all-pairs cosine similarity between \
centroid embeddings. A value near 1.0 means two artists produce semantically \
near-identical work in aggregate, while a value near 0 means their outputs \
occupy very different regions of embedding space. The full heatmap for 100 \
creators gives an overview: warm blocks along the diagonal indicate groups of \
similar creators, while isolated cool rows mark stylistically unique artists. \
The zoomed-in labelled view of the top 25 creators (by work count) makes it \
possible to identify specific artist-to-artist affinities \[LongDash] for \
instance, whether members of the same workshop or school cluster together.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"68b26bbf-0d84-41b5-af23-729625811cef"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
creatorSimMat = centroidMatrix.Transpose[centroidMatrix];

(* Full matrix heatmap *)
MatrixPlot[creatorSimMat,
  PlotLabel -> \"Creator Centroid Cosine Similarity (\" <> \
ToString[nCreators] <> \" creators)\",
  ColorFunction -> \"TemperatureMap\",
  PlotLegends -> Automatic,
  ImageSize -> 600]\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[245]:=",ExpressionUUID->"1b2a364d-e13b-4bf1-a995-bae092f46784"],

